The paper discusses efficient methods for unsupervised learning of probabilistic models, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on energy-based models and their training, which is a subfield of deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses methods for evaluating and comparing models, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory), and methods for generating samples, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
